{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "JobPosting", "baseSalary": {"@type": "MonetaryAmount", "currency": "VND", "minValue": "15000000", "maxValue": "25000000", "unitText": "MONTH"}, "industry": "Cơ khí / Ô tô / Tự động hóa, CNTT - Phần mềm, CNTT - Phần cứng / Mạng", "jobBenefits": "Chế độ bảo hiểm, Phụ cấp, Chăm sóc sức khỏe, Tăng lương, Nghỉ phép năm", "datePosted": "2021-03-30", "validThrough": "2021-04-28", "occupationalCategory": "Nhân viên", "description": "Manufacturing Engineer is responsible for design, operate, and ensuring MODMO manufacturing process running smoothly with the guaranteed efficiency and quality. The Candidate will work closely with R&amp;D department to ensure new product transfer to manufacturer work according to plan and they will choose the best process and technologies to manufacture it, involve in design of process at the factory that will produce it, and manage the running, and continuously improvement of the manufacturing process.You will be working as part of a young team in a very dynamic environment. This means that things sometimes change unexpectedly, and we have to adapt accordingly - but of course we do this as a team. You will not spend the entire time behind a desk but regularly be out to our production factory to ensure the production working as plan.Essential Duties and ResponsibilitiesIn charge of ensuring the product from manufacturing meets the criteria from R&amp;D.Collaborate with R&amp;D team to develop manufacture process for IoT device on e-bike (eg. GPS tracking, 4G/BLE connectivity, Smart display...)Prototyping and implement tooling for testing IoT device in manufacturing/assembling, including hardware, firmware and software development (eg. jig test tooling) to maximize automated test, ensure to control both quality and quantity for production.Manage parts/components quality and quantity coming from supplier before processing assembly.Carrying out Quality assurance test on new design/model/tooling.Ensuring master sample being delivered from all the manufacturer and assisting them on preparing all the documents for QA department.Negotiating with vendors/suppliers to secure the best deal.Analyzing the current method of production and create new ways of producing products by conducting a research, improving the knowledge of the product.Train manufacturing/assembly factory to get better understanding of the new product.Troubleshooting and taking charge into making decision.", "experienceRequirements": "Language: You will be working directly with Europeans so reasonable English is a must.Minimum 3-5 years of relevant work experience with IoT/embedded device development and production.Strong background in programming, including embedded in C/C++/Python, Winform or window desktop app in C# or any relevant language.Experience in hardware development with OrCAD/Altium/KiCAD, including but not limited to design (schematic/layout), prototyping, evaluation, validation, and production.Experience in MCU firmware development for AT Mega, ARM MCU (SAM/STM32/TI/nRF51,52…), ESP8266/32, SCB Rasp PI/Beagle, including all generic peripherals (GPIO, UART, SPI, I2C, USB…), both on Arduino platform for fast prototyping or bare-metal SDK for code size/speed optimization, as well as many cross compliers (GCC/ARMCC) and IDE with debugging equipment (Eclipse/CubeMX/Keil…)Experience in development with RTOS, communication protocol (TCP/IP/HTTP/FPT, MQTT, BLE…) and versioning control with git.Must have experience in working with manufacture workflow/procedure, good mindset in system architecture, automated production / testing development.Good to excellent communication skills with the ability to influence, negotiate, and resolve conflict.Ability to define problems, collect data, draw rational conclusions as well as recommend solution.Excellent in 2D/3D AutoCAD or Solidwork.", "educationRequirements": "Đại học", "qualifications": "Đại học", "identifier": {"@type": "PropertyValue", "name": "Modmo",